Ensure only 1 PreservationObject is made per Resource.

comments.body:
Query run on the console:
```
SELECT metadata #>> '{"preserved_object_id",0,"id"}' as rid, COUNT(*)
FROM orm_resources orm 
WHERE internal_resource = 'PreservationObject'
GROUP BY rid
HAVING orm.count > 1
```

Found 8609 resources with two or more PreservationObjects.
https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1nhuTwoFj0w8Bsv1OA9Lw2-UK3qDW54nCpqc4Iv4JsUA

Example: This [FileSet](https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/0002c3b1-ae6a-4a79-a75a-658841356189) has two related PreservationObjects.

b60878bf-05db-4b07-9204-8d18a3eb987d 
dcd45a8e-79e2-4899-9037-a16f2cce28db

Query to get created dates in descending order:
```
WITH ids AS (
	SELECT metadata #>> '{"preserved_object_id",0,"id"}' as rid, COUNT(*)
	FROM orm_resources orm 
	WHERE internal_resource = 'PreservationObject'
	GROUP BY rid
	HAVING orm.count > 1
)
SELECT orm.id, orm.created_at, ids.rid
FROM (
	SELECT * FROM orm_resources
	WHERE internal_resource = 'PreservationObject'
	) as orm
INNER JOIN ids	
ON ids.rid = orm.metadata #>> '{"preserved_object_id",0,"id"}'
ORDER BY orm.created_at DESC
```

The most recent PreservationObjects created for the same Resource resource are linked to this Coin:
https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/6c6994a7-4abd-4b6b-8488-38b128fb70c2

The PreserveResourceJob was queued 5 times in a 4 minute span.

![Screenshot 2022-12-06 at 3 52 28 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/784196/206032032-7fba5f88-ba02-4b66-9133-a1905a557c6a.png)

**Theory** A Coin is created and marked complete. Changes are made and saved multiple times before any other additional PreserveResourceJobs have completed. A new preservation object is created here on each job invocation:
https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/1c3e9ae220157e4294b7fde634e0dfec8d27f713/app/services/preserver.rb#L78

This would presume that the Coin has no member FileSets because the PreserveResourceJob is run synchronously when a Resource has members.

https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/d7d7e9bc945a4c96d483d7e6d1cc173f9fcd6c5a/app/change_set_persisters/change_set_persister/preserve_resource.rb#L20-L21

The resources were all created and marked complete, but with private visibility. At that point, the UpdateDaoJob would have run:
https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/d7d7e9bc945a4c96d483d7e6d1cc173f9fcd6c5a/app/change_set_persisters/change_set_persister/update_aspace_dao.rb#L10-L14

According to this theory, when they were later made public (and we do see a BulkUpdateJob from Nov 29th making them public), they were not "recently published" at that point, so the UpdateDaoJob wasn't run at all.

Question: Is there any reason we can't just check for a public readable state and not check for the state change? I.e. Is it bad to run that job multiple times?

The affected items are about 2 thousand resources from https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/3c3d2cb3-bc58-4782-84c6-d70df7e36bde. We may need to re-queue the job for all the resources in that collection

to enqueue the members of that collection:

```ruby
qs = ChangeSetPersister.default.query_service
id = Valkyrie::ID.new("3c3d2cb3-bc58-4782-84c6-d70df7e36bde")
resources = qs.custom_queries.find_by_property(property: :member_of_collection_ids, value: id, lazy: true)
resources.each do |r|
  UpdateDaoJob.perform_later(r.id.to_s)
end
```

@ccleeton we updated the logic so this won't happen again in the future, and reran the dao creation for that collection. they appear to be resolved; if there are any stragglers check again later this afternoon since the findingaids incremental index job runs every hour and there may have been a few that weren't done yet at 2pm.
